column5: Maybe $18,000 with the trade-in? I've dinged my fair share of props, but only lost one lower unit, many moons ago. Never again, I hope!
Well if you're a glass half full type at least the one was left to get them home.
Barrie police trailering accident again???
What is the broken part in the very top right of the first photo and then isolated in the second?
I think that might be expensive.
Could have been twice as pricey.
That's probably the CG boat from Brit, lol.

That's the transom mount bracket but I can't for the life of me imagine how it could have been damaged. I wonder if this boat fell while loading it into a storage rack? Perhaps it was hit by another vehicle?
I'm going to find out how it happened tomorrow
But other than that the trip went well?    :-)

Look around inside the boat for a box full of busted parts.  If he hit something in the water to cause that damage, he likely would not be able to find the bottom end.  If it was a trailering incident, I would think he would have grabbed the rest of the bottom end to scavenge parts.
If he hit something in the water, the odds are the other motor wouldn't be untouched (Or the bottom of the boat for that matter)

I hit a rock with the bottom of the skeg while on plane. I snapped the lower off at about a 45 degree angle. We were at a boat in lodge and managed to get to the lodge on the TM. We got a tow back. Found a rebuilt lower in Ft. Francis and was back in the water in 2 days. If I remember correctly the repair was about $2500. The positive was that just before the rock jumped in front a wolf swam across the lake in front of us and we watched it climb out on to the bamk.
Dude hit a Dead Head at WOT on the Ottawa River.......$ 13,000 to repair !!  $ 18,000 for a new engine.........They went with a NEW ENGINE $$$$$$$$$
Where would you find a new 250 Yammie for $18,000 ??
Maybe a government agency was given a discount!!  Edited... to say, just googled and depending model number extension.. $17,800 to $20,000.
Does look like most dealers on our side of the border are looking for about 26 grand MSRP. Guess the Kbec police shop state side...
Take another peak at the trailer.....Ontario Plates !!!
Should be covered by insurance, shouldn't it?
What would the motor be worth as is?
Ten cents a pound.
Looks like someone took a sharp turn or a corner too wide and brought the back end out of the channel into a stump judging by the damage.  Must of been on a boaters card blitz.
I think we are the lucky ones as taxpayers.
